race.comment: Metro-trained PRINCE MAGNETITE (3) was cruelled by a wide gate at Geelong and didn't do a bad job to finish as close as he did. Jumps from an inside barrier today and is heading the right way. He finds the right race. ABBY'S CROSSWORD (5) was beaten a whisker twice at Ballarat and then dropped back to a sprint at Geelong and didn't finish it off. The 1400m suits better, and she should enjoy a soft run from an inside barrier. Well-placed and has each-way claims. ADAMANA (6) gives away starts but wasn't beaten far at Donald when she didn't have the best of it. Has been kept on the fresh side and should be hitting the line hard. HIS LADY BAY (13) raced well in town before the spell and third up benefits from the inside draw and Yendall's engagement. Has the blinkers on for the first time and she can feature in this.
